data.name: label16.Text
data.value: If a guest damages the hotel’s property (e.g., furniture, fixtures, linens), the hotel may charge the guest to cover the repair or replacement costs. This policy ensures that the property is maintained and that guests are responsible for any harm caused during their stay. Always take care to avoid damaging the room or its contents.

data.name: label14.Text
data.value: Hotels often have specific policies regarding smoking and pets, either allowing or prohibiting them in certain areas. Violating these policies may result in fines or eviction. It's important to confirm these restrictions when booking if you plan to bring pets or need a smoking room.

data.name: label12.Text
data.value: Please be advised that only credit card payments are accepted for all transactions. No cash, check, or other forms of payment will be honored. This policy ensures a smooth and efficient payment process for all parties involved.

data.name: label9.Text
data.value: This means that once you book the room, you are not allowed to cancel the reservation. If you cancel after booking, you will not receive a refund. This policy is often applied to discounted or special-rate bookings where the hotel commits to the reservation in advance.
